JOHANNESBURG - At least 3, 000 Toys R Us workers in the United Kingdom will be out of a job from Thursday. The toy chain will be shutting down all of its 100 UK stores after administrators failed to find a buyer for the collapsed retailer. Last month the group appointed Moorfields Advisory as overseer. READ: Fujifilm says to slash 10,000 jobs at Fuji Xerox subsidiary The retail sector has had a dismal start to 2018, with the collapse of Toys R Us and Maplin. A host of other firms are also undergoing painful restructuring, including New Look, Byron and Prezzo and eateries run by celebrity chef Jamie Oliver. Falling consumer spending, soaring Brexit-fuelled inflation and online competition are mostly to blame for the downturn. eNCA